article.headline: Maryland 86, Delaware St. 58
article.story: COLLEGE PARK, Md. -- Landon Milbourne scored a career-high 23 points, and three other Maryland players reached double figures Friday night in an 86-58 rout of Delaware State. The Terrapins (7-2) never trailed in their third straight victory. Maryland is 5-0 at home and 58-4 in non-conference home games since the start of the 2002 season. Up by 19 at halftime, the Terps opened the second half with a 7-0 run to make it 47-21. Eric Hayes led the charge, sinking a pair of 3-pointers around a free throw by Adrian Bowie. Milbourne went 9-for-12 from the floor, made all five free throws and grabbed seven rebounds. Greivis Vasquez had 16 points, eight rebounds and seven assists, and Hayes and Bowie each scored 12. Kris Douse scored 14, and Arturo Dubois had 12 points and eight rebounds for Delaware State (2-11). The Hornets are 0-10 on the road this season.
